 "description": "Keep a per-player record, the referee checking off weeks: a dungeon expedition = 1 week; wilderness adventure = 1 move per day; 1 actual week = 1 game week. Dungeon time covers preparation and a one-day descent; wilderness time includes rest. Time passes for those mewed in their keeps as it does for those in the pits — but not for players out on a wilderness adventure.",
